                    <h4>&#9432; Salzwedel satellite camp</h4>
                    <p>
                        In 1944, a camp that had previously been used for Eastern European forced laborers was converted 
                        into a women’s satellite camp of the Neuengamme concentration camp. The approximately 1,500 prisoners 
                        had to perform forced labor in an armaments company. On April 14, 1945, American troops were able to 
                        liberate the camp to which prisoners from other satellite camps had previously been deported.
                    </p>
